column5: was wondering if anyone knew what these are called  they dont have any writting on them
Do not worry fish cannot read  , just use them.

I can't remember what they are called but I know I had one years ago and it ran like crap. Always pulled to one side and when you went fast, it rolled over. No way to tune them either if I remember correctly.

The Green on is a Luhr Jensson (sp) Power Dive... apparently they don't make them any more... if you don't want it, I'll take it to Quinte with me this fall and show you how it really is!!! LOL If you can find a yellowish one, they are a great bait for fall Picker-eyes! The red one looks like a Bagley. (sp) HH

Those are Luhr Jensen lures. The fat bodied one is called Hot Lips. The longer bodied bait is called the Power Dive Minnow.  I've caught some nice bass & walleye on both the Hot Lips & Speed Traps.   http://www.luhrjensen.com/
Luhr-Jensen Hot Lips Express. Wanna give me one?? Top one is about 15 foot diver. They are real good to have.  luhr-jensen
Hey guys... I asked first!LOL HH

the green one is a powerdive minnow and the red is a hot lips express  but im not sure if its a1/4  1/2  or 3/4 ounce, i use the the 3/4 and with 100-150 feet in back of the boat it dives ove 30 feet deep.  i found a place that has them in texas  so i ordered a bunch i finally got them after 3 months on backorder. the hot lips is my number one  eye/bass trolling bait
thanks guys  what about this one     they will all be up for grabs in the classified section very shortly i have 22 hot lips 4 powerdives and 1 unknown
i think there called fishing lures.those one look good for catching walleye.
i think the last crankbait you posted is a manns 30+
whatever they are, they're all too small.  When the lip is bigger than the bait you're undersized
